fields.description:
The "commit" tab is either disappeared or will have this error :
{noformat}
Error rendering 'com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-bitbucket-connector-plugin:dvcs-commits-tabpanel'. Please contact your JIRA administrators
{noformat}
In addition of that, the DVCS administration page will be un-accessible and displays the following in the attached screenshot

For DVCS Connector version 0.15.11 it requires an OAuth to be setup even for public repositories, or else it throws this error when trying to sync the public GitHub repository:

{code}
Sync Failed: com.atlassian.jira.plugins.bitbucket.api.Authentication$1 cannot be cast to com.atlassian.jira.plugins.bitbucket.api.impl.GithubOAuthAuthentication
{code}

This is for JIRA 4.x.x

Working on a branch, topic-branch. Make a commit on that branch, tag it with a smart commit message to transition it:

{{git commit -m 'ISSUE-123 #transition-one'}}

Check out master, merge in topic branch with a smart commit message to perform a second transition:

{{git checkout master}}
{{git merge -m 'ISSUE-123 #transition-two' topic-branch}}

Expected:
ISSUE-123 is now in the "transition-two" workflow state. The activity tab shows both the transition-one and the transition-two workflow changes in order.

Actual:
ISSUE-123 is in the "transition-one" workflow state. The activity tab shows both workflow changes, but the transition-two change was applied first.

h3. Steps to reproduce:
# Setup JIRA with DVCS Connector;
# Set a BitBucket or GitHub account;
# Configure the same GitHub username and mail into JIRA;
# Enable the smart commits on DVCS Connector;
# Try to perform a commit as per the described below:
{noformat}
"JIRAPROJ-123 my comment #time 1h"
{noformat}

h3. Expected behavior:
# The commit should be displayed on the "Activity" tab and it must have 1 hour logged on Time Tracking; [This page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BITBUCKET/Enabling+DVCS+smart+commits] links to a FishEye page with all the reserved words used on the smart commits. It should be working according to our documentation.

h3. Current behavior:
# The commit is displayed on the "Activity" tab but no work hour has been logged;
# The same exact procedure works for FishEye.

Issue cloned from https://sdog.jira.com/browse/JSTDEV-475

On the View Issue page, if we click the "Bitbucket" tab, all tabs will disappear, and exceptions about a missing column "project_key" are seen in the JIRA log.

